Let's choose the C++ data structures.
`students` can be a `std::unordered_map<std::string, Student>` or `std::map<std::string, Student>`.
`Student` can be a struct:
```cpp
struct Student {
    std::string name;
    int grade;
    std::string major;
    std::unordered_map<std::string, int> courses;
};
```

Wait, `get_gpa` returns `None` in Python. In C++, we can return `std::optional<double>`.
`get_all_students_with_fail_course` returns a `std::vector<std::string>`.
`get_course_average` returns `std::optional<double>`.
`get_top_student` returns `std::optional<std::string>`.

